<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1058,1549,1600]" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[565,645,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">flavidus</emphasis>
, is a Latin name with a meaning of &quot;yellowish&quot;; with reference to the yellow forebody of these beetles.
</paragraph>
